            "answer_text": "Chewing gum has been shown to have many useful effects.   Increase salivary flow - more saliva in your mouth will reduce how long acids are sitting and acting on your teeth.Cleaning off teeth mechanically - the gum will actually help clean the crevices of your teeth.Bad effects This can overload your temporo-mandibular joint (TMJs). In people who already have some type of disorder of their TMJ, chewing gum and other hard foods are usually avoided.",
