            "answer_text": "Chewing gum is good and bad both. Good because of many reasons such as 1.Stimulates flow of saliva, flushing action of saliva keeps the mouth clean. 2.Gums which contain XYLITOL are known to be anti cariogenic and demineralize to an extent. 3.Its sort of an Oral exercise. Bad because 1.Gums with high amount of sucrose, which is the arch enemy of tooth, cause decay at a rapid rate. 2.Excess of chewing gum can get you TMJ pain and discomfort. 3. Some chewing gums are known to be made up of animal fat. ",
